STUDENT PERFORMANCE PREDICTION SYSTEM USING MACHINE LEARNING

1. INTRODUCTION

Student Performance Prediction System is a machine learning-based application developed to predict whether a student is likely to pass or fail based on academic and behavioral factors. The system analyzes student data such as study hours, attendance percentage, sleep hours, assignment scores, and overall scores. Educational institutions can use this system to identify weak students at an early stage and provide necessary support.

2. OBJECTIVE

The main objective of this project is:

• To predict student academic performance.
• To identify students who are at risk of failing.
• To assist teachers in monitoring student progress.
• To improve educational decision-making using machine learning techniques.

3. PROBLEM STATEMENT

Educational institutions often face difficulties in identifying students who may perform poorly in examinations. Manual analysis of student records is time-consuming and may not provide accurate insights. This project aims to automate the prediction process using machine learning algorithms.

4. DATASET DESCRIPTION

The dataset contains the following attributes:

• study_hours_per_day
• attendance_percentage
• sleep_hours
• assignment_score
• overall_score
• final_exam_score

Target Variable:

Result
Pass = 1
Fail = 0

Students scoring 50 or above in the final examination are classified as Pass, otherwise Fail.

5. SYSTEM MODULES

5.1 Data Input Module
Loads student data from CSV files.

5.2 Data Processing Module
Processes and prepares data for machine learning.

5.3 Model Training Module
Trains the Random Forest Classifier using training data.

5.4 Prediction Module
Predicts whether a student will pass or fail.

5.5 Visualization Module
Displays graphs and charts for data analysis.

6. METHODOLOGY

Step 1: Data Collection
Student records are collected from datasets.

Step 2: Data Preprocessing
The target variable "Result" is created from final examination scores.

Step 3: Feature Selection
Selected Features:
• Study Hours Per Day
• Attendance Percentage
• Sleep Hours
• Assignment Score
• Overall Score

Step 4: Train-Test Split
Training Data = 80%
Testing Data = 20%

Step 5: Model Training
Random Forest Classifier is trained using the training dataset.

Step 6: Prediction
The model predicts Pass or Fail for new student records.

Step 7: Evaluation
Performance is measured using:
• Accuracy
• Precision
• Recall
• F1-Score
• Confusion Matrix

7. MACHINE LEARNING ALGORITHM

Random Forest Classifier

Random Forest is an ensemble learning algorithm that builds multiple decision trees and combines their outputs to improve prediction accuracy. It reduces overfitting and provides better performance compared to a single decision tree.

Advantages:
• High accuracy
• Handles large datasets
• Reduces overfitting
• Supports feature importance analysis

